Definition.WordDefinition: Durham \Dur"ham\, n. One or a breed of short-horned cattle, originating in the county of Durham, England. The Durham cattle are noted for their beef-producing quality.
Durham n 1: a city of north central North Carolina; site of Duke University 2: English breed of short-horned cattle [syn: {shorthorn}]
